# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-abc123...        (‚Üê YOUR ACTUAL KEY)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-xyz789... (‚Üê YOUR ACTUAL KEY)  
# XAI_API_KEY=xai-def456...               (‚Üê YOUR ACTUAL KEY)
# HUGGINGFACE_API_TOKEN=hf_ghi789...      (‚Üê YOUR ACTUAL KEY)
# DEFAULT_LLM_PROVIDER=openai

# Example 3: Enterprise Setup (With Monitoring)
# ---------------------------------------------
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-enterprise123... (‚Üê YOUR ACTUAL KEY)
# TRACK_API_USAGE=true
# DAILY_BUDGET_LIMIT=100.00
# ENABLE_PERFORMANCE_MONITORING=true
# MIN_TEST_COVERAGE=90

# =============================================================================
# üîß ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE REFERENCE
# =============================================================================

# | Variable | Required | Default | Description |
# |----------|----------|---------|-------------|
# | `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | Yes* | - | OpenRouter API key for multi-model access |
# | `OPENROUTER_MODELS_TO_USE` | Yes* | - | Comma-separated list of models for 3-LLM panel |
# | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | No | - | Direct OpenAI API access |
# | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | No | - | Direct Anthropic API access |
# | `XAI_API_KEY` | No | - | Direct xAI (Grok) API access |
# | `HUGGINGFACE_API_TOKEN` | No | - | Hugging Face token for embeddings |
# | `DEFAULT_LLM_PROVIDER` | No | `openrouter` | Default provider selection |
# | `AUTO_COMMIT_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable automatic Git commits |
# | `ENFORCE_CONSTITUTION` | No | `true` | Enable spec-driven quality gates |
# | `MIN_TEST_COVERAGE` | No | `85` | Minimum test coverage percentage |
# | `DEBUG_MODE` | No | `false` | Enable detailed logging |

# *Either OpenRouter keys OR individual provider keys are required.

# =============================================================================
# üö® SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# =============================================================================

# 1. **Never commit `.env` files** - They contain sensitive API keys
# 2. **Use different keys for development/production** - Separate environments
# 3. **Rotate API keys regularly** - Update keys periodically for security
# 4. **Monitor API usage** - Keep track of costs and usage patterns
# 5. **Use secure storage** - Enable `USE_SECURE_STORAGE=true` in VS Code

# =============================================================================
# üéØ GETTING API KEYS
# =============================================================================

# OpenRouter (Recommended)
# ------------------------
# 1. Visit https://openrouter.ai/keys
# 2. Sign up or log in
# 3. Create a new API key
# 4. Copy the key (starts with `sk-or-v1-`)
# 5. Replace REPLACE_ME_WITH_YOUR_ACTUAL_OPENROUTER_KEY above

# Individual Providers
# -------------------
# - OpenAI: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# - Anthropic: https://console.anthropic.com/
# - xAI (Grok): https://console.x.ai/
# - Hugging Face: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens

# =============================================================================
# ‚ö†Ô∏è COMMON ISSUES TO AVOID
# =============================================================================

# 1. DO NOT use placeholder values like:
#    - "your-key-here"
#    - "your-enterprise-key"
#    - "sk-or-v1-your-key"
#    These will cause 401 authentication errors!

# 2. DO NOT have multiple entries for the same variable
#    The last entry will override previous ones

# 3. DO NOT include quotes around your API keys
#    ‚ùå OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-v1-abc123"
#    ‚úÖ OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-abc123

# 4. DO NOT commit this file if you add real keys
#    Always use .env (which is gitignored)

